        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "If last param in uri is empty - http:\/\/example.com\/controller\/action\/param1\/some_value\/param2\/\/\r\ngetParams() or getParam() method from request class doesn't return this param (param2) and when the uri is like this: http:\/\/example.com\/controller\/action\/param1\/\/param2\/some_value2\/ param1 is declared but empty. I've noticed it in ZF 1.9.7 but this bug also has influence on 1.10 and maybe other versions.\r\n\r\nThis problem has a source in Zend_Controller_Router_Route_Module::match() method. Match() body trims a path to clear trailing and ending self::URI_DELIMITER:\r\n{code}$path = trim($path, self::URI_DELIMITER);{code}\r\nand when the uri is like this: http:\/\/example.com\/controller\/action\/param1\/some_value\/param2\/\/ the result is: controller\/action\/param1\/some_value\/param2\r\nThen \"for\" loop determines if some value exist after param2 and because of trim it doesn't exist so the null value is assigned to param2\r\nUnfortunately Zend_Controller_Request_Abstract::setParam() use unset for those params (whith null values):\r\n\r\n{code}if ((null === $value) && isset($this->_params[$key])) {\r\n    unset($this->_params[$key]);\r\n} elseif (null !== $value) {\r\n    $this->_params[$key] = $value;\r\n}{code}\r\n\r\nmy suggestion is to replace code from Zend_Controller_Router_Route_Module::match():\r\n\r\n{code}$val = isset($path[$i + 1]) ? urldecode($path[$i + 1]) : null;{code}\r\n\r\nto this one:\r\n\r\n{code}$val = isset($path[$i + 1]) ? urldecode($path[$i + 1]) : '';{code}\r\n\r\n\r\nin this way the last empty param should have the same value like the empty param in the middle of path.\r\n\r\n"
        },
